NATURE

“The bubbling brook doth leap when I come by, Beeause my feet find measure with its call;

The birds know when the friend they love is nigh, For I am known to them, both great and small. The flower that on the lonely hillside grows Expeets me there when spring its bloom has given, And many a tree and bush my wanderings knows,

And e’en the clouds and silent stars of heaven;” —Jones Very.
